# Local build output (produced by `dagger call server-binary -o ./bin/...`).
/bin/

# templ's generated Go (*_templ.go) is committed, not ignored: the build
# pipeline does not run `templ generate`, so a fresh checkout must already
# contain it. Run `templ generate` after editing a .templ file.

# Terraform runs inside a container (`dagger call terraform ...`), so none of
# this should exist in a checkout — but it does the moment someone runs the
# CLI here directly, and a stray *.tfvars is how a project id and an email
# get committed. State never lands on disk at all: the backend is GCS.
#
# .terraform.lock.hcl is NOT ignored. It pins the provider builds by hash,
# for every platform the module might run on, and committing it is what makes
# an apply from CI and an apply from a laptop the same apply.
.terraform/
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
*.tfvars
*.tfvars.json
crash.log
